  "description": [
    "VOLUME 22 ifi in Santiagos Fortifications Riddled by Shot and Shell HE REIN MERCEDES WRECKED Many Spanish Officers Killed or Fatally Wounded LAND FORCES ARE ALSO SUCCESSFUL New York June 8 A dispatch from Cape Haytien describing the bombardment of Santiago de Cuba on Monday says that the forts about the harbor are now a mass of ruins The Morro is a shapeless pile of ruined masonry and dismantled guns and the Estrella battery is utterly ruined This result the dispatch says was the work of 10 American ironclads which passed back and forth from Port Cabrera on the west to Port Aguadores on the east of the harbor entrance discharging their heavy guns as they steamed along so that scarcely a yard of the coast escaped the deadly cannonading ISlown to Dust At Port Aguadores the fort recent ly constructed by Col Ordonez the famous artillery expert was blown to dust and Col Ordonez himself was badly wounded by the flying splinters and debris Captain Sanchez and Lieut Yrizar artillery officers were also wounded Two infantry lieutenants Garcia and Perez and 21 privates are report ed fatally wounded Wreckod tlic Mercedes Later in the day the American ships moved"
